The article discusses the defense cooperation between the United States and Brazil. It mentions the establishment of the U.S.-Brazil Defense Cooperation Dialogue (DCD) and the upcoming meeting between Secretary of Defense Panetta and Minister of Defense Amorim. The article highlights the U.S.-Brazil Defense Cooperation Agreement, which promotes cooperation in areas such as research and development, logistics support, and technology security. It also mentions the General Security of Military Information Agreement, which facilitates the sharing of classified defense and military information. The article further discusses military exercises and exchanges, including training on disaster response and cyberdefense, as well as multinational air and naval exercises. It emphasizes the cooperation between the U.S. and Brazilian militaries in providing relief during the Haiti earthquake and the exploration of greater military cooperation relating to Africa. The article also mentions the proposal to sell F/A-18E/F Super Hornet fighter aircraft to Brazil's Air Force.